  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Helicobacter pylori eradication (H. pylori) rates with clarithromycin-based triple therapy
      are declining, and an alternative strategy is needed urgently. The investigators sought to
      compare the efficacy of pretreatment antimicrobial susceptibility-guided vs.
      clarithromycin-based triple therapy vs. concomitant therapy for H. pylori eradication in a
      region with high rates of multiple drug resistance.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
